==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Cuckolds knot
<hw>Cuck"old's knot`</hw> <pr>(k?k"?ldz n?t`)</pr>. <fld>(Naut.)</fld>
<def>A hitch or knot, by which a rope is secured to a spar, the two
parts of the rope being crossed and seized together; -- called also
<altname>cuckold's neck</altname>.</def> <rj><au>Ham. Nav.
Encyc.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cuckoo</ent>⟦br⟧
